---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
import familyPhoto from '../assets/chris-trish-concert.jpg';
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`About - ${SITE_TITLE}`}
  description="About Chris Kaelin - grandfather, tech enthusiast, and family man from Kentucky"
>
  <div class="about-page">
    <!-- Left Sidebar -->
    <aside class="about-sidebar">
      <img src={familyPhoto.src} alt="Chris and Patricia Kaelin" class="about-photo" />
      <h1 class="about-name">Chris & Patricia</h1>
      <p class="about-tagline">Parents · Grandparents · Kentucky</p>
    </aside>

    <!-- Right Content -->
    <div class="about-content">
      <div class="about-section">
        <h2>Who We Are</h2>
        <p>
          Hey there! We're Chris and Patricia Kaelin, and welcome to our little corner of the internet. We're proud
          grandparents, lifelong learners, and family-first people living in the beautiful Bluegrass State of Kentucky.
          Being grandparents to Cecily and August has been one of life's greatest joys — there's nothing quite like
          seeing the world through a child's eyes again or watching them discover something new for the first time. Our
          daughter Peyton and son-in-law Joel keep us on our toes too. Whether we're having Sunday dinners, planning
          family adventures, or just spending quiet time together, these moments are what matter most. Chris's path here
          has been anything but straight. After serving in the Air Force and spending years building software, he
          discovered that what he loves most isn't just the coding — it's the problem-solving, the "aha!" moments, and
          sharing what he's learned with others. Whether he's helping our church with their live stream setup, building
          something new for fun, or teaching Cecily and August how computers work, technology is just another way to
          bring people together.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-section">
        <h2>Life Beyond the Screen</h2>
        <p>When Chris is not tinkering with code or we aren't trying new food/recipes, you'll find us:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Playing with our grandchildren (and probably getting schooled at video games)</li>
          <li>Trying new recipes and perfecting old family favorites</li>
          <li>Cheering for our favorite teams—win or lose, we're loyal</li>
          <li>Serving at church and helping with their technology needs</li>
          <li>Taking walks around our beautiful Kentucky neighborhood</li>
          <li>Reading, learning something new, or planning the next family adventure</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="about-section">
        <h2>Things We're Working On</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Family Time</strong> – The most important project of all. Planning gatherings, teaching grandchildren something
          new, or just being present for the people we love.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Side Projects</strong> – This site is a perfect example — Chris built it from scratch because we wanted
          a place that truly reflected who we are as a family. That's how he thinks: the best way to learn is by building
          things, even if they're just for us and the people we love.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Our Church</strong> – We're both part of the behind the scenes leadership team, and Chris helps the tech
          side. Whether it's live streaming services or helping with the website and social media, it's rewarding work that
          serves our community.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-section">
        <h2>Let's Be Friends</h2>
        <p>We love connecting with people who share similar interests or just want to chat about life.</p>
        <p>
          <strong>Email</strong>: <a href="mailto:chris@kaelinfamily.com">chris@kaelinfamily.com</a><br />
          <strong>GitHub</strong>: <a href="https://github.com/christopherkaelin" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
            >github.com/christopherkaelin</a
          ><br />
          <strong>LinkedIn</strong>: <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/christopherkaelin/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener">linkedin.com/in/christopherkaelin</a
          >
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
